{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''RahXephon'' media}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}} This is a '''list of media''' from the Japanese [[science fiction]] series '''''[[RahXephon]]'''''.
''RahXephon'' began production as an [[anime]] [[television series]] in 2001. A [[manga]] version, a [[novelization]], [[soundtrack]]s and an [[audio drama]] were published during and after the original broadcast, which lasted from January to September 2002. The series was released on [[DVD]] in Japan during its original broadcast, and was subsequently translated and both broadcast and released on DVD in other countries.
<onlyinclude>A television movie, a ''RahXephon'' video game, and an [[Original video animation|OVA]] episode were released a year later, in 2003. Characters, mecha and story from ''RahXephon'' were featured in a game in the ''[[Super Robot Wars]]'' series. Art books, guide books and additional novels were also released. </onlyinclude>This list includes video games and music, but not toys, hobby articles and other merchandise.
==Printed media== ===Manga volumes===<!--This section is linked from [[RahXephon]]--> {{See also|RahXephon#Manga|RahXephon#Book reviews}} The manga release started before the anime broadcast, so that the ending in one medium would not trail too far behind the other.<ref name="ntusabuchi">{{cite journal | last = Wong | first = Amos | authorlink = | coauthors = |date=February 2003 | title = Interview with Yutaka Izubuchi | journal = [[Newtype USA]] | volume = 2 | issue = 2 | pages = 14–15 | doi = | issn = 1541-4817 }}</ref> The first chapter, or "mission", appeared in the magazine ''[[Monthly Sunday Gene-X]]'' in the October 2001 issue<ref>{{cite web | title=This month's number of Sunday GX | url=http://www.websunday.net/gx/number/kongetu.html | language=Japanese | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20011007101939/http://www.websunday.net/gx/number/kongetu.html|archivedate=2001-10-07 }}</ref> (released 19 September 2001); the final chapter was released two months after the airing of the last anime episode, in the December 2002 issue (released 19 November 2002).<ref>{{cite web|title=This month's number of Sunday GX |url=http://www.websunday.net/gx/number/kongetu.html |language=Japanese |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20021204062953/http://www.websunday.net/gx/number/kongetu.html |archivedate=4 December 2002 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Next number of Sunday GX | url=http://websunday.net/gx/number/jigou.html | language=Japanese | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20021213191609/http://websunday.net/gx/number/jigou.html|archivedate=2002-12-13}}</ref>
